                                         skos:definition "Specifically for digital pathology, formats such as .svs or .tif store high-resolution tissue scans in a \"pyramidal\" structure to allow access at various zoom levels."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00135
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00135> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00059> ;
                                         dc:source <https://www.bic.mni.mcgill.ca/software/minc/> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "Based on HDF5, this format is highly efficient for very large, complex medical datasets often used in academic brain research."@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "MINC"@en ,
                                                    "MINC"@es ,
                                                    "MINC"@zh ;
                                         skos:definition "Medical Imaging NetCDF (MINC) is a medical imaging data format and also an associated set of tools and libraries."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00136
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00136> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap#ROADMAP_03644> ,
                                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03302> ;
                                         dc:source <https://arxiv.org/abs/1706.08500> ,
                                                   <https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cviu.2021.103329> ;
                                         rdfs:label "Fréchet inception distance"@en ,
                                                    "Fréchet inception distance"@zh ,
                                                    "distancia de inicio de Fréchet"@es ;
                                         skos:altLabel "FID"@en ,
                                                       "弗雷歇起始距离"@zh ;
                                         skos:definition "Fréchet inception distance compares the distribution of generated images with the distribution of a set of real images. Rather than comparing individual images, mean and covariance statistics of many images generated by the model are compared with the same statistics generated from images in the reference set."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00137
