                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 0. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00143
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00143> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03545> ;
                                         rdfs:label "adjusted Rand index"@en ,
                                                    "adjusted Rand index"@zh ,
                                                    "Índice de Rand ajustado"@es ;
                                         skos:altLabel "ARI"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The Adjusted Rand Index (ARI) is a cluster validation metric measuring similarity between two data clusterings by evaluating all pair-wise sample assignments, corrected for chance. Ranging from -1 to 1, an ARI of 1 indicates perfect agreement, 0 represents random labeling, and negative values indicate worse-than-random performance"@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> -1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00144
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00144> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap#ROADMAP_03642> ,
                                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03302> ;
                                         dc:source "https://doi.org/10.1109/TPAMI.1979.4766909"@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "Davies-Bouldin index"@en ,
                                                    "Davies-Bouldin 指数"@zh ,
                                                    "índice de Davies-Bouldin"@es ;
                                         skos:altLabel "DBI"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The Davies–Bouldin index (DBI) is a metric for evaluating clustering algorithms, where the validation of how well the clustering has been done is made using quantities and features inherent to the dataset."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00145
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00145> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04043> ;
