                                         skos:definition "An item from the TRAM-AI (Transparency in Reporting of Medical Imaging datasets for Artificial Intelligence) checklist."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00191
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00191> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03342> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-023-02151-z> ,
                                                   <https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-8137.1912.tb05611.x> ;
                                         rdfs:label "intersección de máscara sobre unión > 0"@es ,
                                                    "mask intersection over union > 0"@en ,
                                                    "掩码交并比 > 0"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "mask IoU > 0"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "Mask intersection over union > 0 determines whether a predicted region shares at least one pixel with the reference region. It operates as a binary localization criterion, indicating only the presence or absence of spatial overlap. This metric provides an extremely permissive threshold for detection tasks where coarse positional matching is sufficient."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> "false"^^xsd:boolean ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> "true"^^xsd:boolean .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00199
