###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00463
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00463> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00248> ;
                                         dc:source <https://www.oecd.org/en/topics/sub-issues/ai-principles.html> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "The OECD AI Principles are the first intergovernmental standard on AI. They promote innovative, trustworthy AI that respects human rights and democratic values. Adopted in 2019 and updated in 2024, they are composed of five values-based principles and five recommendations that provide practical and flexible guidance for policymakers and AI actors [from OECD web site]."@en ,
                                                      "The OECD AI Principles identify five complementary values-based principles for the responsible stewardship of trustworthy AI."@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "OECD AI principle"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The OECD AI Principles are a framework adopted in 2019 by the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development to promote trustworthy and human-centered artificial intelligence. They guide governments and organizations in developing, deploying, and managing AI systems that are fair, transparent, and accountable."@en .


