###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03487
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03487> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03491> ;
                                         rdfs:label "auxiliar médico de radiología"@es ,
                                                    "radiology physician assistant"@en ,
                                                    "放射科医师助理"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "RPA"@en ,
                                                       "radiology practitioner assistant"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "A Radiology Physician Assistant (PA) or Radiology Practitioner Assistant (RPA) is a licensed, advanced-practice healthcare professional who works under radiologist supervision to enhance patient care in imaging departments. They specialize in conducting patient assessments, performing image-guided interventional procedures, assisting with image interpretation, and managing patient safety (e.g., contrast administration)."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03488
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03488> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03491> ;
                                         rdfs:label "auxiliar de radiología"@es ,
                                                    "radiology assistant"@en ,
                                                    "放射科助理"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "RA"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "A Radiologist Assistant (RA) is an advanced-practice registered radiologic technologist who works under radiologist supervision to enhance patient care, perform imaging procedures, and manage patient assessments."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03489
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03489> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00075> ;
                                         rdfs:label "oncólogo radioterapeuta"@es ,
                                                    "radiation oncologist"@en ,
                                                    "放射肿瘤学家"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "radiation therapist"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "A radiation oncologist is a specialized physician who uses high-energy radiation (such as X-rays, gamma rays, or protons) to treat cancer and some non-cancerous conditions."@en ;
                                         skos:exactMatch <http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/SNOMEDCT/763292005> .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03490
