                                                       "radiation therapy medical physicist"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "A radiation therapy physicist (or radiation oncology physicist) is a specialized healthcare scientist who applies principles of physics to ensure the safe and accurate delivery of high-energy radiation for cancer treatment."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03495
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03495> rdf:type owl:Class ;
