###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03605
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03605> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00015> ;
                                         rdfs:label "tratamiento"@es ,
                                                    "treatment"@en ,
                                                    "治疗"@zh ;
                                         skos:definition "Medical treatment is the management, care, and application of measures (such as drugs, surgery, or therapies) to combat, cure, prevent, or ameliorate a disease, injury, or health condition. It involves actions taken by healthcare providers to improve a patient's health or manage symptoms."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03606
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03606> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00015> ;
                                         rdfs:label "cura"@es ,
                                                    "cure"@en ,
                                                    "治愈"@zh ;
                                         skos:definition "A cure is a method, medicine, or treatment that restores health by eliminating a disease or illness,"@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03607
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03607> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00015> ;
                                         rdfs:label "mitigación"@es ,
                                                    "mitigation"@en ,
                                                    "缓解"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "risk mitigation"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "Mitigation in health refers to actions taken to reduce the severity, pain, or harmful effects of illnesses, injuries, or hazards before or during an event. It involves identifying and managing risks to improve patient safety, minimize disease spread (e.g., social distancing), and prevent long-term damage."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03608
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03608> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00015> ;
                                         rdfs:label "prevención"@es ,
                                                    "prevention"@en ,
                                                    "预防"@zh ;
                                         skos:definition "Prevention in health refers to actions, policies, and interventions aimed at reducing the risk of disease, injury, and disability, as well as minimizing their burden."@en .


