###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04003
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04003> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03624> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "\"Designed to be used by humans as well as machines, DOIs identify objects persistently. They allow things to be uniquely identified and accessed reliably. You know what you have, where it is, and others can track it too.\""@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "digital object identifier"@en ,
                                                    "identificador de objeto digital"@es ,
                                                    "数字对象标识符"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "DOI"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "A digital identifier of a physical, digital, or abstract object. For example, \"10.1148/ryai.240200\"."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00155> "[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+(\\.[0-9]+)?\\/.*" ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03626> <https://doi.org/$> .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04004
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04004> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03624> ;
                                         rdfs:label "PubMed identifier"@en ,
                                                    "PubMed标识符"@zh ,
                                                    "identificador de PubMed"@es ;
                                         skos:altLabel "PMID"@en ,
                                                       "PubMed ID"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The unique identifer of an article available through PubMed. For example, the identifier \"38809149\" specifies the URL https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38809149/."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00155> "[0-9]+" ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03626> <https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/$> .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04005
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04005> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03391> ;
                                         rdfs:label "surgical video"@en ,
                                                    "vídeo quirúrgico"@es ,
                                                    "手术视频"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "operative video"@en ,
                                                       "procedural video"@en ,
                                                       "surgery video"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "Video images of surgical procedure."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04006
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04006> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03634> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1073445.1073465> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-N"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-N"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-N"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation - N-gram Co-Occurrence Statistics"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-N calculates the recall of n-gram overlaps between a candidate summary and a set of reference summaries. It is computed as the ratio of the total number of matching n-grams to the total number of n-grams in the reference summaries, favoring summaries that align with the consensus among references. Higher-order n-grams capture more word order information, while unigrams focus on content coverage."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04007
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04007> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04006> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1073445.1073465> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-1"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-1"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-1"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation – Unigram Co-Occurrence Statistics"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-1 evaluates the similarity between a generated text and a reference text based on the overlap of unigrams. It calculates recall, precision, and F-measure using individual word matches to quantify content coverage."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04008
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04008> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04006> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1073445.1073465> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-2"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-2"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-2"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation – Bigram Co-Occurrence Statistics"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-2 evaluates the similarity between a generated text and a reference text based on the overlap of bigrams. It measures matching two-word sequences to capture both content and limited word order information, reporting recall, precision, and F-measure."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04009
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04009> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03634> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1218955.1219032> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-L"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-L"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-L"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation - Longest Common Subsequence"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-L measures similarity based on the Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) between candidate and reference texts. It accounts for word order without requiring consecutive matches, capturing sentence-level structure naturally. Scores are computed using LCS-based recall and precision combined into an F-measure, making ROUGE-L robust to variations in word placement while rewarding in-sequence matches."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04010
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04010> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04009> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1218955.1219032> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-W"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-W"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-W"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation - Weighted Longest Common Subsequence"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-W is an extension of ROUGE-L that applies Weighted Longest Common Subsequence to emphasize consecutive matches. By assigning higher scores to longer uninterrupted sequences, ROUGE-W distinguishes summaries with contiguous phrases from those with fragmented word order, improving sensitivity to fluent expression while maintaining structural evaluation."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04011
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04011> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03634> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1218955.1219032> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-S"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-S"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-S"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation - Skip-Bigram Co-Occurrence Statistic"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-S evaluates similarity using skip-bigrams, which are pairs of words in correct order but not necessarily adjacent, allowing for flexible gaps. This approach captures both lexical content and approximate word order, offering more nuanced matching than fixed n-gram methods. Scores are based on the overlap of skip-bigrams and can be adjusted with constraints on maximum skip distance to reduce spurious matches."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04012
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04012> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                         rdfs:subClassOf <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04011> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.3115/1218955.1219032> ;
                                         rdfs:label "ROUGE-SU"@en ,
                                                    "ROUGE-SU"@es ,
                                                    "ROUGE-SU"@zh ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Recall-Oriented Understudy for Gisting Evaluation - Skip‑Bigram plus Unigram"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "ROUGE-SU extends ROUGE-S by incorporating unigram matches in addition to skip-bigrams. This ensures that even when skip-bigram matches are absent, partial credit is awarded for individual word matches, making it suitable for very short or structurally varied summaries."@en ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00274> 1. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03651> 0. ;
                                         <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_03652> 1. .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04013
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_04013> rdf:type owl:Class ;
