###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00253
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00253> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "universality"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "U"@en ,
                                                       "universal"@en ,
                                                       "universality principle"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The U in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should be developed and validated on diverse, representative populations to ensure broad applicability."@en ,
                                                         "The universality principle states that a medical AI tool should be generalizable outside the controlled environment where it was built. Specifically, the AI tool should be able to generalize to new patients and users, and when applicable, to new clinical sites."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00254
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00254> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "traceability"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "T"@en ,
                                                       "traceability principle"@en ,
                                                       "traceable"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The T in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should be transparent, with full documentation of data, methods, and results to support auditability."@en ,
                                                         "The traceability principle states that medical AI tools should be developed together with mechanisms for documenting and monitoring the complete trajectory of the AI tool, from development and validation to deployment and usage."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00255
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00255> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "explainability"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "E"@en ,
                                                       "explainability principle"@en ,
                                                       "explainable"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The E in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should provide explanations that are clinically meaningful and understandable to end users."@en ,
                                                         "The explainability principle states that medical AI tools should provide clinically meaningful information about the logic behind the AI decisions."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00256
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00256> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "usability"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "US"@en ,
                                                       "usability principle"@en ,
                                                       "usable"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The U(s) in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should be designed for practical, effective use in real clinical workflows."@en ,
                                                         "The usability principle states that the end users should be able to use an AI tool to achieve a clinical goal efficiently and safely in their real world environment."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00257
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00257> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "robustness"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "RO"@en ,
                                                       "robust"@en ,
                                                       "robustness principle"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The R in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should perform reliably and safely across diverse clinical settings and patient populations."@en ,
                                                         "The robustness principle refers to the ability of a medical AI tool to maintain its performance and accuracy under expected or unexpected variations in the input data."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00258
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00258> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00249> ;
                                         rdfs:label "fairness"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "FA"@en ,
                                                       "equitable"@en ,
                                                       "equity"@en ,
                                                       "fair"@en ,
                                                       "fairness principle"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "The F in FUTURE-AI: AI solutions should perform equitably across demographic subgroups and avoid discriminatory outcomes."@en ,
                                                         "The fairness principle states that medical AI tools should maintain the same performance across individuals and groups of individuals."@en .


