                                         skos:altLabel "Minimum Information about Clinical Artificial Intelligence Modeling"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "MI-CLAIM (Minimum Information about Clinical Artificial Intelligence Modeling) is a reporting framework developed to standardize how clinical artificial intelligence (AI) and machine-learning models are described, evaluated, and shared. It aims to ensure transparency, reproducibility, and comparability across medical AI research, enabling better validation and clinical translation of algorithms"@en .


