                                         skos:definition "PROBAST+AI (Prediction model Risk Of Bias ASsessment Tool for Artificial Intelligence) is an international methodological initiative that extends the original PROBAST framework. It provides structured guidance for evaluating risk of bias and applicability in studies that develop or validate AI-based prediction models, particularly in health research."@en .


###  https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00489
<https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00489> rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                  <https://rsna.org/roadmap/ROADMAP_00174> ;
                                         dc:source <https://doi.org/10.1038/s41591-021-01517-0> ,
                                                   <https://doi.org/10.2196/58202> ;
                                         rdfs:comment "QUADAS-AI guideline is in development (as of 2026-06-01)."@en ;
                                         rdfs:label "QUADAS-AI"@en ;
                                         skos:altLabel "Quality Assessment of Diagnostic Accuracy Studies - AI extension"@en ,
                                                       "Quality Assessment of Diagnostic Accuracy Studies using Artificial Intelligence"@en ,
                                                       "artificial intelligence–specific quality assessment of diagnostic accuracy studies"@en ;
                                         skos:definition "QUADAS-AI is an extension of the Quality Assessment of Diagnostic Accuracy Studies (QUADAS) tool, specifically designed to evaluate bias and applicability in studies involving artificial intelligence (AI)–based diagnostic systems. It provides a structured, standardized approach to assess methodological quality when machine learning is used for clinical diagnosis or image interpretation."@en .


